# Pocket Dictionary

A command-line tool for building your personal dictionary and learning new words.

## Features

- Look up word definitions from an online dictionary API.
- Organize words into custom groups.
- Test your knowledge with interactive quizzes.
- Weighted testing system to focus on words you find more difficult.

## Installation

1.  Clone this repository:
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/pocket-dictionary.git
    cd pocket-dictionary
    ```

2.  Install the dependencies:
    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

## Usage

The script is controlled via command-line arguments.

### General Syntax

```bash
python pocket_dictionary.py [command] [arguments]
```

### Commands

-   **`lookup <word>`**: Looks up a word's definition and adds it to your dictionary.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Specify a group to add the word to (default: "default").

-   **`add <word>`**: Manually adds a word to a group without looking it up.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Specify a group (default: "default").

-   **`remove <word>`**: Removes a word from a group.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Specify the group to remove the word from.

-   **`add_group <group_name>`**: Creates a new, empty group.

-   **`remove_group <group_name>`**: Deletes a group and all the words within it.

-   **`list`**: Lists all of your word groups and the number of words in each.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Lists all the words within a specific group.

-   **`random`**: Starts a random word quiz. You'll be shown a word and prompted to press Enter for the definition.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Quizzes you only on words from the specified group.

-   **`test`**: Starts a word guessing test. You'll be shown a definition and must guess the corresponding word.
    -   `--group <group_name>`: Tests you only on words from the specified group.

### Examples

-   Look up the word "ephemeral" and add it to the "vocabulary" group:
    ```bash
    python pocket_dictionary.py lookup ephemeral --group vocabulary
    ```

-   List all words in the "default" group:
    ```bash
    python pocket_dictionary.py list --group default
    ```

-   Start a test on words from all groups:
    ```bash
    python pocket_dictionary.py test
    ```

## Data Storage

Your word lists and groups are stored in a JSON file located at `~/.pocket_dictionary/groups.json`.